From Joe Hildebrand Subject Re question regarding overlaying of graphics Let's say I have two rectangles on the canvas see above one intersecting the Now I would like to delete one of the The way I do it is to create another GC wherein I use the GXxor logical function and simply redraw the rectangle using the newly created graphics context thus deleting it for all apparent A problem with this approach is that at the points of intersection the pixel locations belonging to the other rectangle also become white which is something that should be You could set up a bitmap with a mask in Clear the bitmap draw the rectangle to be deleted with Draw the one that is to stay with Then GXxor the entire pixmap with the Note that this is a pretty effective way of animation if you ever need to do that replace the GXclear with a GXxor Joe Hildebrand Software Engineer Fuentez Systems Concepts Standard disclaimers apply